{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781714204987,"sessionID":"ses_12999e669ffe1hL4934q4NiLtx","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_cef2a5704e90489e816d8719","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/nathangreen/Development/eddi-lab/llm-orc/scratch/spike-tau-long-horizon/ladder/gate-b/workspaces/arm-f5-cc8b124d/README.md","content":"# Temperature Conversion Library  \nA small Python library for converting temperatures between Celsius, Fahrenheit, and Kelvin with a command-line interface.  \n\n## Installation & Usage  \nInstall via pip (if packaged) or use directly from source.  \n\n### CLI Examples  \n```bash  \npython cli.py 100 C F  # Converts 100°C to Fahrenheit  \npython cli.py 32 F C   # Converts 32°F to Celsius  \n```  \n\n### Supported Conversions  \n| From    | To      |  \n|---------|---------|  \n| Celsius | Fahrenheit |  \n| Fahrenheit | Celsius |  \n| Celsius | Kelvin |  \n\n### CLI Arguments  \n`python cli.py <value> <from_unit> <to_unit>`  \nValid units: `C`, `F`, `K`  \n\n## Running Tests  \n```bash  \npython -m pytest test_converters.py test_cli.py  \n# or  \npython -m unittest test_converters.py test_cli.py  \n```  \n\n## Programmatic Usage  \nImport conversion functions from `converters.py`:  \n```python  \nfrom converters import celsius_to_fahrenheit  \nresult = celsius_to_fahrenheit(25)  \nprint(result)  # Output: 77.0  \n```"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/nathangreen/Development/eddi-lab/llm-orc/scratch/spike-tau-long-horizon/ladder/gate-b/workspaces/arm-f5-cc8b124d/README.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"scratch/spike-tau-long-horizon/ladder/gate-b/workspaces/arm-f5-cc8b124d/README.md","time":{"start":1781714204964,"end":1781714204985}},"id":"prt_ed67139150010BHYLuAJx01hpy","sessionID":"ses_12999e669ffe1hL4934q4NiLtx","messageID":"msg_ed67052c3001ttaKxv5V4vgP0e"}}
